creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 139 by Various.
Read in English by Shakira Searle; Garth Burton; Chris Pyle; Glenn O'Brien; Thomas A. Copeland; Bruce Kachuk; Winston Tharp; Nancy Jane Thompson; DomBombadil; Faith Pak; Son of the Exiles; Peter Tucker; Algy Pug; Lucy Perry
This is a collection of 24 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for December 2014. This collection includes the following:
Alms, by Edna St. Vincent Millay Ballade of Christmas-boxes, by F. Ritchie Ballade of Christmas Ghosts, by Andrew Lang The Dance of Death, by Charles Baudelaire The Day Before I Die, by Henry Lawson The Exequy, by Henry King God Save The Flag, by Oliver Wendell Holmes, Sr. The Highwayman, by Alfred Noyes How Do I Love Thee? (Sonnet 43), by Elizabeth Barrett Browning A Hymn of Peace, by Oliver Wendell Holmes, Sr. I Wandered Lonely As a Cloud, by William Wordsworth Jeptha's Daughter, by George Gordon, Lord Byron Lady Clare, by Alfred, Lord Tennyson The Mahogany-Tree, by William Makepeace Thackeray The Men We Might Have Been, by Henry Lawson On Monsieur’s Departure, by Queen Elizabeth I On the Morning of Christ's Nativity, by John Milton Piano, by D. H. Lawrence Stone-Broke, by A. H. Beesly Strictly Germproof, by Arthur Guiterman To a Common Prostitute, by Walt Whitman Ulysses, by Alfred, Lord Tennyson Uphill, by Christina Rossetti Sonnet V (What lips my lips have kissed), by Edna St. Vincent Millay For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
